den John Kent & compt
Sence my last of 26 past rec. yor of 10 ditto, if you can
dett no nothrens to my patt.N3 & 6 then lett them numbers
be to the inclosed patt. for I will have non made expresseley
there by detaine the complenting of my order from the
north, from whence you send mee to nvoyce of N1 with kerly
the prises there of are deaver then I exspected & others informe
mee, Itake notice that you will go on ou ys termes & not serve
mee in commission, I do not show yo inbention, & why my monney
& correspondent is not as good as that of mr. Roosendael B
his cosen & there by pr walter promised mee when here you should
serve mee in commission, I know not when wee shall have convoy
from ostend, butt when one comes lett a pack of cottons be ship
ped 8 demie reds and 5 whites from 22 to 24 pence non
excceding 24 pence supposeinge that com is now cheapst att
last as cheap as 4 monthes ago: buy also a pack to containe
6 white swanskins bayes oft the lesser sort of about 6os &
8 a 50 ditto of 66 half of the greenstreephen in the lest &
half of the broather sort, with 4 fines devous hire bayes
the finest & whitest that are to be had of 2 ƒ a yd. red liste
adding in the same pack 4 severall white penestons of 4
several prices for atryall, non of the least, neithernon of
the finest for I have some spiculation upon them sort of goods
towards sommer. draw no on mee as I have wrett you
before & advose what passes whilst I res
lett my pack bee well wy apped with cottons of 20, a 21 4 a 22
